#### JS OO ####

1) Zugriff auf super-Methoden
- via Referenz auf prototype-Objekt (proto)

2) call() mit Übergabe von this-Referenz:
- erforderlich, wenn super-Methoden aufgerufen werden

3) bind() mit Angabe von this:
- für Event Listener auf DOM Elementen, innerhalb derer this verwendet wird
- generell: für alle Callback-Funktionen

4) bind() must only be used within lifecycle methods
- if subtypes are used, it cannot be used successfully within the constructor of a supertype - see showMenu()/hideMenu() in mwf.SidemenuViewController
- ???

5) attention: lifecycle functions do not use camel case, but complete lower case

6) callback functions should not require call using call(this,...) as here, this should be bound already

7) do not forget to always call callbacks if they are passed!

8) JSON.stringify must not be called on objects that presumable are or contain entities - if entities are passed, they might expose cyclic values, and the error message on submit might not be visible!

9) in ractive templates, existence / nonexistence (for update/create mode) must be checked calling created() on item and passing the id ("this" does not work inside of this calls...?)

10) ractive templates should be instantiated with a container (e.g. args), not with the model object itself as otherwise update might not work correctly (see Readview for Note und MediaItem)


####

embedded view controllers with mwf-initialise-onload should not use templates (as they are currently initialised before templates are read out...)

####
OO:
- managed attributes can be declared in supertypes
- instantiateManagedAttributes() must be called by bottom-most types, but can be kept in supertypes (does not seem to do harm...)
- for polymorphism, type declaration of managed attribute is not enough... type needs to be set on pojo (as in json for java/jaxrs)